             <h1>Talenthon Token Sale Agreement</h1>
    <br>

    <p><strong>Talenthon Token Sale Agreement</strong></p>

    <p><strong>Last Updated: February 14, 2018</strong></p>

    <p>This Talenthon Token Purchase Agreement (this &ldquo;<ins>Agreement</ins>&rdquo;) contains the terms and conditions that govern your use of the Talenthon Platform and purchase of the Talenthon tokens (the &ldquo;<ins>TALEN Tokens</ins>&rdquo;) distributed on the Ethereum blockchain. This Agreement is made&nbsp; between you or the entity that you represent (&ldquo;<ins>Buyer</ins>&rdquo; or &ldquo;<ins>you</ins>&rdquo;) and Talenthon O&Uuml;, Private Limited Company, incorporated in Estonia (together with its affiliates, &ldquo;<ins>Company</ins>&rdquo;).&nbsp; Buyer and Company are herein referred to individually as the &ldquo;<ins>Party</ins>&rdquo; and collectively as the &ldquo;<ins>Parties</ins>&rdquo;.</p>

    <p>NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual representations, warranties, and agreements contained in this Agreement, and for other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which are hereby acknowledged, Company and Buyer agree as follows:</p>

    <p><strong>IMPORTANT: PLEASE READ THIS AGREEMENT CAREFULLY AND IN ITS ENTIRETY.</strong></p>

    <p>Buyer acknowledges, understands, and agrees:</p>

    <ol>
        <li>BINDING AGREEMENT:&nbsp; Buyer understands and agrees that Buyer is subject to and bound by this Agreement by virtue of Buyer&rsquo;s purchase of TALEN Tokens.</li>
        <li>TALEN TOKENS HAVE NO RIGHTS, USES, OR ATTRIBUTES outside of the Talenthon Platform (the &ldquo;Project&rdquo;).</li>
        <li>PURCHASE OF TALEN TOKENS ARE NON-REFUNDABLE AND CANNOT BE CANCELLED.&nbsp;</li>
        <li>BUYER MAY LOSE ALL AMOUNTS PAID.</li>
        <li>TALEN TOKENS MAY HAVE NO VALUE.</li>
        <li>COMPANY RESERVES THE RIGHT TO REFUSE OR CANCEL TALEN TOKEN PURCHASE REQUESTS AT ANY TIME IN ITS SOLE DISCRETION.</li>
        <li>PEOPLE WHO PURCHASE EARLIER THAN YOU MAY RECEIVE MORE TOKENS FOR THE AMOUNT PAID.</li>
        <li>PLEASE READ THE RISKS SET FORTH IN SECTION 13 CAREFULLY AND IN THEIR ENTIRETY.</li>
        <li>THIS AGREEMENT INCLUDES PRE-DISPUTE RESOLUTION IN SECTION 15.1 AND REQUIRES ARBITRATION ACCORDING TO SECTION 15.2.</li>
    </ol>

    <p>&nbsp;</p>

    <p><strong>1. BINDING AGREEMENT</strong></p>

    <p><ins>1.1 Effective Time</ins>. This Agreement shall be effective and binding on the Parties when (a) Buyer clicks the check box on the official <a target="_blank"  href="https://talenthon.io/">https://talenthon.io/</a> website (the &ldquo;Website&rdquo;) to indicate that Buyer has read, understands, and agrees to the terms of this Agreement; or (b) upon Company&rsquo;s receipt of payment from Buyer.&nbsp; Buyer agrees to be bound on this basis, and confirms that Buyer has read in full and understands this Agreement and the terms, on which Buyer is bound.</p>

    <p><ins>1.2 Website Terms of Use</ins>.&nbsp; Company has established Terms of Use, as may be amended from time to time, for the website located at <a target="_blank"  href="https://talenthon.io/terms">https://talenthon.io/terms</a> , which are hereby incorporated by reference.&nbsp; Buyer has read, understands and agrees to those terms.</p>

    <p><ins>1.3 White Paper</ins>.&nbsp; Company has prepared the White Paper and other materials concerning the Project and the sale of TALEN Tokens and they are available at <a target="_blank"  href="https://www.talenthon.io/assets/docs/whitepaper_talenthon.pdf">https://www.talenthon.io/assets/docs/whitepaper_talenthon.pdf</a>. The White Paper may be amended from time to time and is, hereby, incorporated by reference.&nbsp; Buyer has read and understands the White Paper and its contents.</p>

    <p>&nbsp;</p>

    <p><strong>2. TALEN TOKEN </strong></p>

    <p><ins>2.1. Purpose and Use of TALEN Tokens on the Talenthon platform</ins>. Talenthon TOKEN IS NEITHER AN ASSET, NOR A SECURITY. It is a utility token that shall be used in the Company&rsquo;s decentralized Talenthon Platform to access the used vehicle database, to be able to retrieve or provide information about particular vehicle, and to pay transaction or other fees associated with the use of the Talenthon platform. The TALEN token serves as a method of validating the user&rsquo;s interactions with TALEN Platform. For more details about the use of the TALEN Tokens, please refer to the Company&rsquo;s whitepaper at <a target="_blank"  href="https://www.talenthon.io/assets/docs/whitepaper_talenthon.pdf">https://www.talenthon.io/assets/docs/whitepaper_talenthon.pdf</a> )</p>

    <p><ins>2.2. Limited Use of TALEN Tokens</ins>. TALEN Tokens do not have any rights, uses, purpose, attributes, functionalities, or features, expressed or implied, outside of the Talenthon platform. Purchase, ownership, receipt, or possession of TALEN Tokens carries no rights, express or implied, other than the right to use such tokens as a means to participate, interact, or transact on the Company&rsquo;s platform and ecosystem.&nbsp; In particular, Buyer understands and accepts that TALEN Tokens do not represent or confer any ownership right or stake, share, security, or equivalent rights. They also do not confer any right to receive future revenue shares, dividends, other payments, intellectual property rights, or any other form of participation in or relating to the Company and its corporate affiliates, other than any rights relating to the provision and receipt of services from Company, subject to limitations and conditions in this Agreement. The holders of Talenthon token are only entitled to use Talenthon products as described in this document and only if it is successfully developed, or to sale the tokens when they become of no utility to them. Although TALEN Tokens may be tradable, they are not intended to be a digital currency, security, commodity, a swap on a currency, security, or commodity, or any kind of financial instrument. The Talenthon token itself will be based on Ethereum, a blockchain-based computing platform that allows smart contracts &ndash; distributed computer programs which can facilitate online contractual agreements in a cryptographically secure manner.</p>

    <p>&nbsp;</p>

    <p><strong>3. BUYERS</strong></p>

    <p><ins>3.1. Token Receipt Address</ins>. In order to be eligible to participate in the Company&rsquo;s token sale, Buyer must have an Ethereum wallet that supports the ERC-20 standard in order to receive any Tokens purchased from Company (the &ldquo;Token Receipt Address&rdquo;). Company reserves the right to prescribe additional guidance regarding specific wallet requirements.</p>

    <p><ins>3.2. Minimum Age</ins>. In order to be eligible to participate in the Company&rsquo;s token sale, Buyers must be eighteen (18) years of age.</p>

    <p><ins>3.3. Personal Information</ins>. In order to be eligible to participate in the Company&rsquo;s token sale, Buyers must also enter all required personal information in the purchase flow and thereafter, including name, date of birth, address, etc and provide any requested identity verification documents requested by the Company in order to satisfy their &ldquo;know your customer&rdquo; requirements within twelve (12) months of the Buyer&rsquo;s contribution.</p>

    <p><ins>3.4. Acknowledgment and Assumption of Risks</ins>. Buyer acknowledges and agrees that there are risks associated with purchasing TALEN Tokens, owning TALEN Tokens, and using TALEN Tokens for the provision or receipt of services on Company. BY PURCHASING TALEN TOKENS, BUYER EXPRESSLY ACKNOWLEDGES AND ASSUMES THESE RISKS.</p>

    <p><ins>3.5. Buyer&rsquo;s Security</ins>.&nbsp; Buyer will implement reasonable and appropriate measures designed to secure access to:&nbsp; (i) any device associated with Buyer and utilized in connection with Buyer&rsquo;s purchase of TALEN Tokens; (ii) private keys to Buyer&rsquo;s wallet or account; and (iii) any other username, passwords, or other login or identifying credentials.&nbsp; In the event that Buyer is no longer in possession of Buyer&rsquo;s private keys or any device associated with Buyer&rsquo;s account or is not able to provide Buyer&rsquo;s login or identifying credentials, Buyer may lose all of Buyer&rsquo;s TALEN Tokens and/or access to Buyer&rsquo;s account.&nbsp; Company is under no obligation to recover any TALEN Tokens and Buyer acknowledges, understands, and agrees that all purchases of TALEN Tokens are non-refundable and Buyer will not receive money or other compensation for any TALEN Tokens purchased.</p>

    <p><ins>3.6. Personal Information</ins>. Upon Company&rsquo;s request, Buyer will immediately provide to Company information and documents that Company, in its sole discretion, deems necessary or appropriate to comply with any laws, regulations, rules, or agreements, including, without limitation, judicial process.&nbsp; Such documents include, but are not limited to, passport, driver&rsquo;s license, utility bills, photographs of associated individuals, government identification cards, or sworn statements.&nbsp; Buyer consents to Company disclosing such information and documents in order to comply with applicable laws, regulations, rules, or agreements.&nbsp; Buyer acknowledges that Company may refuse to distribute TALEN Tokens to Buyer until such requested information is provided.</p>

    <p><ins>3.7. Taxes</ins>. Buyer acknowledges, understands, and agrees that:&nbsp; (a) the purchase and receipt of TALEN Tokens may have tax consequences for Buyer; (b) Buyer is solely responsible for Buyer&rsquo;s compliance with Buyer&rsquo;s tax obligations; and (c) Company bears no liability or responsibility with respect to any tax consequences to Buyer.</p>

    <p>&nbsp;</p>

    <p><strong>4. ACQUISITION OF TOKENS</strong></p>

    <p><ins>4.1. Acquisition</ins>. On the terms set forth herein, you will agree to purchase and we will agree to sell TALEN tokens. There is no minimum or maximum amount of purchase. Company reserves the right to refuse or cancel tokens purchase requests at any given time in its sole discretion.</p>

    <p><ins>4.2. Accepted Forms of Payment</ins>. Company accepts the following cryptocurrencies for purchase of the TALEN Tokens: ETH, BTC, LTC and DASH.</p>

    <p><ins>4.3. Purchase Amount</ins>. For purposes of TALEN tokens, the value of the purchase amount shall be deemed in ETH whether the Purchaser pays in fiat money or cryptocurrencies valued at the Applicable Exchange Rate for ETH. The term &ldquo;Applicable Exchange Rate&rdquo; shall mean the volume-weighted average daily price of ETH on exchanges in the 24-hour period (Eastern Time) following the day and time that the Company notifies the Buyer, in writing, that the Company has accepted Buyer&rsquo;s offer to purchase the VI Token under this Agreement.</p>

    <p>4.4. TALEN Tokens will be created and provided to you after completion of the Sale Period in relation to the amount of collected financial resources. The general amount of TALEN Tokens created through the smart contract system will depend on the aforementioned factor. All of the TALEN Tokens are of equal value and functionality.</p>

    <p>4.5. The price of TALEN Tokens is nominated in Ethereum at the rate of 1 ETHEREUM = 20000 TALEN tokens + bonus. Upon the end of the Sale Period, the amount of ETH that supports such smart contract will be converted into TALEN Tokens through MetaMask and it will be possible to check the general amount of TALEN Tokens that you own.</p>

    <p>4.6. More details regarding the purchase procedure, the timing, the pricing, and the anticipated use of the TALEN Tokens sale are defined in the Whitepaper.</p>

    <p><strong>5. TALEN TOKEN DISTRIBUTION</strong></p>

    <p><ins>5.1. Allocation and Distribution of TALEN Tokens</ins>.&nbsp; Company intends to allocate and distribute TALEN Tokens (the &ldquo;Token Distribution&rdquo;) in accordance with the White Paper, including, without limitation, that the distribution will take place over several days with earlier buyers receiving more TALEN Tokens for the same amount paid.&nbsp; Company will provide specific procedures on how Buyer may seek purchase TALEN Tokens through the Website.&nbsp; By purchasing TALEN Tokens, Buyer acknowledges, understands, and has no objection to such procedures and specifications.&nbsp; Failure to use the Website and follow such procedures may result in Buyer not receiving any TALEN Tokens.&nbsp; Any buyer of TALEN Tokens may lose some or all of the amounts paid for TALEN Tokens.&nbsp; The access or use of the Talenthon Platform and/or the receipt or purchase of TALEN Tokens through any other means are not sanctioned or agreed to in any way by Company.&nbsp; Buyer should take great care and purchase TALEN Tokens using only Company&rsquo;s official website at <a target="_blank"  href="https://talenthon.io/">https://talenthon.io/</a> .</p>

    <p><ins>5.2. Allocation and Sale of TALEN Tokens to Company Parties</ins>.&nbsp; Buyer understands and consents to the participation of Company&rsquo;s past, present, and future employees, officers, directors, contractors, consultants, equity holders, suppliers, vendors, and service providers in the purchase of TALEN Tokens, including people who may work on the development and implementation of the Project or who may work for Company&rsquo;s future businesses that Company may establish with a portion of the proceeds from the sale of TALEN Tokens.</p>

    <p><ins>5.3. No Representations and Warranties</ins>. Company makes no representations or warranties, express or implied, including, without limitation, any warranties of title or implied warranties of merchantability or fitness for a particular purpose with respect to the Talenthon Platform or the TALEN Tokens or their utility, or the ability of anyone to purchase or use the TALEN Tokens.&nbsp;Without limiting the foregoing, none of the Company Parties represent or warrant that the process of purchasing and/or receiving of the TALEN Tokens will be uninterrupted or error-free or that the TALEN Tokens are reliable and error-free.&nbsp; As a result, Buyer acknowledges and understands that Buyer may never receive TALEN Tokens and may lose the entire amount Buyer paid to Company.&nbsp;</p>

    <p><ins>5.4. Not an Offering of Securities, Commodities, or Swaps</ins>.&nbsp;The sale of TALEN Tokens is not an investment and the TALEN Tokens themselves are not securities, commodities, swaps on either securities or commodities, or a financial instrument of any kind.&nbsp; Purchases and sales of TALEN Tokens are not subject to the protections of any laws governing those types of financial instruments.&nbsp; This Agreement and all other documents referred to in this Agreement, including the White Paper, do not constitute a prospectus or offering document, and are not an offer to sell, nor the solicitation of an offer to buy an investment, a security, commodity, or a swap on either a security or commodity.</p>

    <p><ins>5.5. Not an Investment.</ins>&nbsp; Buyer should not purchase TALEN Tokens or participate in the TALEN Token distribution for investment purposes.&nbsp; TALEN Tokens are not designed for investment purposes and should not be considered as a type of investment. &nbsp;Buyer acknowledges, understands, and agrees that Buyer should not expect (and there is no such guarantee or representation or warranty by Company) that:&nbsp; (a)&nbsp;the Project will ever be adopted; (b) the Project will be adopted as developed by Company and not in a different or modified form; (c) a blockchain utilizing or adopting the Project will ever be launched; and (d) a blockchain will ever be launched with or without changes to the Project.</p>

    <p><ins>5.6. Not for Speculation</ins>.&nbsp; Buyer acknowledges and agrees that Buyer is not purchasing TALEN Tokens for purposes of investment, speculation, as some type of arbitrage strategy, for immediate resale, or other financial purposes.</p>

    <p><ins>5.7.&nbsp; Sources and Uses of Funds.</ins></p>

    <p>(a)&nbsp; <ins>Use of Funds</ins>.&nbsp; Buyer shall not use TALEN Tokens to finance, engage in, or otherwise support any unlawful activities.</p>

    <p>(b)&nbsp; <ins>Payments</ins>.&nbsp; All payments by Buyer under this Agreement shall be made only in Buyer&rsquo;s name, from a digital wallet or bank account not located in a country or territory that has been designated as a &ldquo;non-cooperative country or territory&rdquo; by the Financial Action Task Force, and is not a &ldquo;foreign shell bank&rdquo; within the meaning of the U.S. Bank Secrecy Act (31 U.S.C. &sect; 5311 et seq.), as amended, and the regulations promulgated thereunder by the Financial Crimes Enforcement Network, as such regulations may be amended from time to time.</p>

    <p>(c)&nbsp; <ins>Anti-Money Laundering; Counter-Terrorism Financing</ins>.&nbsp; To the extent required by applicable law, Buyer shall comply with all anti-money laundering and counter-terrorism financing requirements.</p>

    <p><ins>5.8.&nbsp; Transfers</ins></p>

    <p>(a)&nbsp; <ins>Transfer Fees</ins>.&nbsp; Buyer agrees that any transfer of TALEN Tokens may be subject to transfer fees imposed by Company from time to time through Etherium Wire&nbsp; Protocol.</p>

    <p>(b) <ins>Transfer Restrictions</ins>.&nbsp; Buyer agrees that Company may place limitations on the transferability of TALEN Tokens through the Etherium Wire Protocol.</p>

    <p><ins>5.9. Cancellation; Refusal of Purchase Requests.</ins> All TALEN Token purchases from the Company are final, and there are no refunds or cancellations except as may be required by applicable law or regulation. Company reserves the right to refuse or cancel token purchase requests at any time in its sole discretion.</p>

    <p><ins>5.10. Token Allocation</ins>. Important information about the Company&rsquo;s creation and intended use of the TALEN Tokens is provided in the Company&rsquo;s White Paper at <a target="_blank"  href="https://www.talenthon.io/assets/docs/whitepaper_talenthon.pdf">https://www.talenthon.io/assets/docs/whitepaper_talenthon.pdf</a>. By purchasing TALEN Tokens, Buyer acknowledges that Buyer has read and understands the White Paper.</p>

